Make sure you have the `wiringPi` library installed on your Raspberry Pi. You can install it using the following command:

```bash
sudo apt-get install wiringpi
```

And compile the C program using the following command:

```bash
gcc -o distance_sensor distance_sensor.c -lwiringPi -lwiringPiI2C
```

Then run the program:

```bash
./distance_sensor
```

This program will continuously check for an object closer than 200mm and log the detected object's distance and timestamp to a file named `distance_log.txt`.

Please note that you need to calibrate the VL53L1X sensor before using it with the Raspberry Pi. You can refer to the VL53L1X datasheet for more details on how to do this.

Also, the VL53L1X sensor has a range of 50mm to 1000mm. If you want to use a different range, you can change the range register value in the sensor's datasheet.

