This code blinks the LED connected to GPIO 17 every 2 seconds unless a button connected to GPIO 27 is pressed. The button pulls its line up to VCC (3.3V) when not pressed, and to GND when pressed. The program uses the pigpio library to handle GPIO, and sets up an interrupt function to handle the button press. When the button is pressed, the buttonState variable is set to 1, and the LED will not blink. When the button is not pressed, the buttonState variable is set to 0, and the LED will blink every 2 seconds.

Make sure to install pigpio library before running this program. You can install it using the command:

```bash
sudo apt-get install pigpio
```

And compile the program using gcc:

```bash
gcc -o blinky blinky.c -lpigpio -lrt
```

Then run the program:

```bash
sudo ./blinky
```

This program assumes that you have a LED connected to GPIO 17 and a button connected to GPIO 27 on your Raspberry Pi. You may need to adjust the pin numbers if your hardware is connected differently.

Please note that the button press will not be detected when the program starts because the button is set to pull up, and the GPIO library will not trigger an alert for the initial state of the button.

