This program uses the wiringPi library to interact with the GPIO pins on the Raspberry Pi. The PIR sensor is connected to GPIO 17 and the LED is connected to GPIO 18. The `wiringPiISR` function is used to set up an interrupt service routine (ISR) that is called every time the PIR sensor state changes. The `myInterrupt` function toggles the state of the LED depending on the state of the PIR sensor. If the PIR sensor is triggered, the LED is turned on. If the PIR sensor is not triggered, the LED is turned off.

Remember to compile the code with `gcc -o motionDetector motionDetector.c -lwiringPi -lpthread -lrt`.

