This code sets the DAC output to 2.5V using the MCP4725 DAC. The DAC value is sent as two bytes to the MCP4725 over I2C. The high byte is the command and control byte, and the low byte is the DAC value. The command and control byte is constructed by setting the lower 4 bits to 0 (write to DAC command), the lower 4 bits of the DAC value to 1 (buffered), and the upper 2 bits to 1 (power-down command).

This code assumes that the bcm2835 library is installed and the MCP4725 is connected to the Raspberry Pi's I2C bus. If the library is not installed, it can be installed using the command `sudo apt-get install raspberrypi-kernel-headers` and `sudo apt-get install libbcm2835-dev`. If the MCP4725 is not connected, it can be connected using the appropriate I2C pins on the Raspberry Pi.

Please note that the DAC value is set to 0x3FFF (4095 in decimal) to output 2.5V. You can change this value to output a different voltage. The value is shifted right 4 bits to form the high byte and shifted left 4 bits to form the low byte.

